Standard and Poor's Corp said itdowngraded to B-plus from A about 50 mln dlrs of collateraltrust notes of Leaseway Transportation Corp.    S and P cited a leveraged buyout offer from an investorgroup that was organized by Citibank and included management.    The buyout of Leaseway will result in significantdeterioration of its balance sheet, the agency pointed out.    Leaseway's strong competitive position in auto hauling andretail support services will enable it to generate sufficientcash flow to service commitments. But S and P expects debtleverage to remain extremely high for the forseeable future. Reuter&#3;